            ">Cyclone pummels French territory</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-17-1.jpg" alt="Cyclone pummels French territory" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Rescue workers are dashing to aid Mayotte, a French Indian Ocean territory, after Cyclone Chido, the strongest storm in nearly a century, <a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/news/mayotte-cyclone-chido-french-overseas-territory-deaths/" target="_blank">devastated</a> the region. The archipelago encountered intense winds of at least 140 mph. While the official death toll is 14, authorities fear hundreds or thousands more may have died. The island, home to 300,000 people, suffered catastrophic damage, with slum settlements and infrastructure like hospitals and airports destroyed.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Due to damage to the airport control tower, military aircraft are the only means of access, and electricity remains shut across the archipelago. Aid is being sent from France and nearby Réunion. French President Emmanual Macron said France would have a <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/france/20241216-rescuers-race-to-reach-survivors-in-french-territory-of-mayotte-after-cyclone" target="_blank">national mourning</a> period and visit Mayotte. The French Red Cross reports that about 100,000 residents living in makeshift homes lost everything. Experts link the storm's intensity to climate change, noting that warmer air and seas fuel stronger storms.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
